Here's how to handle each scenario:

**1. Windows-only tests — use `[TestCategory]` + conditional skip:**

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[TestCategory("WindowsOnly")]
[DoNotParallelize] // registry access may need serialization
public void Registry_ReadsExpectedValue()
{
    if (!OperatingSystem.IsWindows())
        Assert.Inconclusive("Requires Windows registry.");

    // ... test logic
}
```

Or with .NET 5+, use a platform-check attribute on the method and filter at the runner level.

**2. Skip in CI (requires local GPU):**

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[TestCategory("RequiresGPU")]
public void Render_ProducesExpectedOutput()
{
    if (Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("CI") == "true")
        Assert.Inconclusive("Skipped in CI — requires local GPU.");

    // ... test logic
}
```

Then in CI you can also filter these out entirely:

```bash
dotnet test --filter "TestCategory!=RequiresGPU"
```

**3. Flaky external API — retry with `[DataRow]` isn't built-in, so use `[Retry]` (MSTest v3.8+) or a manual pattern:**

```csharp
// MSTest 3.8+ (recommended)
[TestMethod]
[Retry(3)] // retries up to 3 times on failure
public void Weather_ReturnsForecast()
{
    var result = _weatherClient.GetForecast("Seattle");
    Assert.IsNotNull(result);
}

// Pre-3.8 manual fallback
[TestMethod]
public void Weather_ReturnsForecast_Manual()
{
    Exception? last = null;
    for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++)
    {
        try
        {
            var result = _weatherClient.GetForecast("Seattle");
            Assert.IsNotNull(result);
            return; // passed
        }
        catch (Exception ex) { last = ex; }
    }
    Assert.Fail($"Failed after 3 attempts: {last!.Message}");
}
```

**4. Cleanup even on failure — use `[TestCleanup]` or `try/finally`:**

```csharp
[TestClass]
public class TempFileTests
{
    private string? _tempFile;

    [TestInitialize]
    public void Setup()
    {
        _tempFile = Path.GetTempFileName();
    }

    [TestCleanup] // runs even if the test fails or throws
    public void Cleanup()
    {
        if (_tempFile != null && File.Exists(_tempFile))
            File.Delete(_tempFile);
    }

    [TestMethod]
    public void Process_WritesToTempFile()
    {
        File.WriteAllText(_tempFile!, "data");
        var result = MyProcessor.Process(_tempFile!);
        Assert.IsTrue(result.Success);
    }
}
```

For one-off cases, `try/finally` inside the test also works.

**Summary:**

| Scenario | Approach |
|---|---|
| Platform-specific | `Assert.Inconclusive()` + `[TestCategory]` |
| Skip in CI | Env-var check + `--filter` at the runner |
| Flaky external deps | `[Retry(N)]` (v3.8+) or manual loop |
| Cleanup on failure | `[TestCleanup]` (class-level) or `try/finally` |
